                future phases get analogous bundle specs : spec-71 Phase-B · spec-72 Phase-C · etc.

§I THESIS
  ⟦
    Phase-A closes the WinMain-class bug structurally. Twelve items collectively make it impossible
    for a csslc-built .exe to ship with dead user-main code, impossible for type-shape mismatches
    to be silently rejected, impossible for cross-target struct layouts to drift, impossible for
    diagnostics to fail to point at the offending source span.
    
    Items are tightly coupled : item-01 (sentinel-return) needs item-03 (symbol-audit) to verify
    user-main is reachable · item-02 (recognizer-type-mismatch) needs item-89 (diagnostics-with-carets)
    to produce useful error messages · item-08 (cross-target-struct-parity) needs item-09 (σ-enforce
    extended) to verify FFI boundary layouts. Bundling them in one spec keeps the coupling visible.
    
    Phase-A is the foundation of the revenue-unblock slice. It must land before math-half-Phase-B
    (spec-71). Until Phase-A is VERIFIED, every PR risks shipping dead code (the WinMain class).
    Gate-E (scripts/sentinel_build_check.sh) is the structural backstop · this spec is the items
    that make Gate-E's job easy.
  ⟧

