§I OBSERVABLE-ASSERTIONS [MANDATORY]
  ⟦
    item-01 ASSERTs :
      A01.1 · csslc-rt prologue writes 0xC0FFEE to %CSSL_SENTINEL_PATH% before user-main runs
      A01.2 · csslc-rt epilogue writes 0xDEADBEEF after user-main returns (covers normal-exit path)
      A01.3 · scripts/sentinel_build_check.sh exits 0 PASS on cssl-built .exe with both magic bytes present
      A01.4 · sentinel_build_check.sh exits 2 DEGRADED if exe alive but contract not-honored (transitional)
    
    item-02 ASSERTs :
      A02.1 · `csslc compile bad.cssl` where bad.cssl has `fn f(x : u32) -> i64 { x }` fails with
              diagnostic mentioning "expected i64, got u32" + source span pointing at `x`
      A02.2 · the canonical test cases for type-shape regression land in csslc/tests/recognizer/
      A02.3 · no silent-fall-through path in cssl-mir::body_lower for type-mismatch (audit pass)
    
    item-03 ASSERTs :
      A03.1 · csslc post-codegen pass walks the emitted .o for the user-main symbol
      A03.2 · pass FAILS the build if WinMain (or _main, _start, mainCRTStartup) is present without
              tail-call to user-main
      A03.3 · golden-test : a known-bad .o (WinMain returns 0 directly) fails this pass with diagnostic
              "WinMain does not tail-call user-main · WinMain-class dead-code risk"
    
    item-04 ASSERTs :
      A04.1 · csslc emits build-manifest.json containing list of expected (symbol-name, hash) tuples
      A04.2 · linker reads manifest before producing .exe · errors with "manifest mismatch: symbol X
              expected hash H, got H'" on any divergence
      A04.3 · CI fails the build if build-manifest.json is missing from build artifacts
    
    item-05 ASSERTs :
      A05.1 · CI test-runner refuses to mark a test PASS if exit=0 AND stdout=∅ AND stderr=∅ AND
              no observable filesystem mutation occurred
      A05.2 · the test-harness exposes `cssl_test_observe(...)` for tests to register expected side-effects
      A05.3 · golden-test : an empty `fn user_main() {}` test fails A05.1 (verified by CI)
    
    item-06 ASSERTs :
      A06.1 · linker cross-checks declared-effect-row of each fn against emitted FFI symbol set
      A06.2 · fn declared `/ { IO }` that emits no IO-FFI-symbol fails link with diagnostic
      A06.3 · fn declared `/ {}` (pure) that emits any IO-FFI-symbol fails link with diagnostic
    
    item-08 ASSERTs :
      A08.1 · csslc test-corpus contains 20 small modules · each compiled to all 5 targets
              (SPIR-V · DXIL · MSL · WGSL · native-x64)
      A08.2 · for each struct used across targets · layout bytes are diffed · max diff = 0
      A08.3 · packed-parity-failure surfaces as csslc-level diagnostic naming the field that drifted
    
    item-09 ASSERTs :
      A09.1 · σ-enforce pass extended to FFI-boundary structs (extern "C" fn signatures)
      A09.2 · alignment violation on FFI boundary emits LAY0002 (per existing spec-33 stable code)
              with FFI-boundary context in the diagnostic
      A09.3 · golden-test : struct with field at offset-misaligned-for-extern-C fails LAY0002
    
    item-19 ASSERTs :
      A19.1 · `let x = if cond { 1 } else { 2 }` parses + compiles in expression position
      A19.2 · works in struct-init context : `let p = Point { x: if cond { 0 } else { 1 }, y: 0 }`
      A19.3 · works in return-position : `fn f() -> i32 { if cond { 1 } else { 2 } }` (no explicit `return`)
      A19.4 · v13 LoA substrate.cssl drops every `clamp((x-y)*1e6, 0, 1)` branchless-flag-trick comment
              after re-compile · regression-frame matches pre-change
    
    item-30 ASSERTs :
      A30.1 · GPU resources (Buffer · Texture · DescriptorSet · Semaphore · Fence) have Drop impls
      A30.2 · scope-exit runs Drop · GPU resource handle returned to host-rt allocator
      A30.3 · valgrind/ASan or equivalent leak-check on a known scope shows zero leaked GPU handles
    
    item-87 ASSERTs :
      A87.1 · csslc per-module hash computed · stored in .cssl-cache/
      A87.2 · re-compile with no source change exits in < 1s (cache-hit on all modules)
      A87.3 · single-module source change re-compiles only that module + dependents · not full tree
    
    item-89 ASSERTs :
      A89.1 · diagnostics include source-file path · line · column · caret pointing at offending token
      A89.2 · diagnostics include "did you mean : X?" suggestion when the user's identifier is within
              edit-distance 2 of a defined identifier
      A89.3 · diagnostics use ANSI color codes when stderr is a tty (RUSTC_COLOR-style)
  ⟧

