§I FAILURE-MODES
  ⟦
    FM.01 · scenario : item-01 csslc-rt contract added but downstream tests don't observe sentinel-bytes
            detection : sentinel_build_check.sh exits 2 DEGRADED · auto-issue raised
            mitigation : ASSERT A01.4 explicitly tracks DEGRADED transitional-state
    
    FM.02 · scenario : item-02 recognizer-tightened breaks existing v13 substrate.cssl
            detection : Role-D substrate validation harness (18 rays) fails post-merge
            mitigation : recognizer changes always paired with grace-period flag · v13 ports forward
    
    FM.03 · scenario : item-08 cross-target-parity reveals existing struct-layout drift
            detection : 20-module test corpus surfaces · failures triaged per-target
            mitigation : drift IS a bug · spec-amendment iff drift was intentional · else fix to parity
    
    FM.04 · scenario : item-30 drop-checker triggers on existing GPU-resource patterns in cssl-host-*
            detection : compile-error post-implementation
            mitigation : grace-period · @no_drop_check escape hatch for stage-0 Rust shims (sunsets at Phase-E)
    
    FM.05 · scenario : item-19 if-expression breaks parser on existing if-statement code
            detection : parser test-corpus regression
            mitigation : if-expression is additive (statement-position works as-before) · type-checker
                          distinguishes context · v13 substrate.cssl is canonical test bed
    
    FM.06 · scenario : items merge faster than ASSERT-clauses verify · race to VERIFIED state
            detection : Gate-C nightly ASSERT-runner shows IMPLEMENTED items without 5-consecutive-pass
            mitigation : VERIFIED state is per-ASSERT · partial-verify is acceptable interim · merge cadence
                          ¬ blocked by VERIFIED · only IMPLEMENTED required to merge
  ⟧

