§I OPEN-QUESTIONS
  ⟦
    OQ.01 · should item-01 sentinel magic bytes be configurable per-build for security?
             default · no · 0xC0FFEE / 0xDEADBEEF are stable forever · these are NOT secrets
    OQ.02 · should item-04 manifest support unsigned-symbol exceptions for FFI to non-CSSL libs?
             default · yes · @opaque_extern marker bypasses manifest check for declared-foreign symbols
    OQ.03 · item-05 run-and-observe : how does it handle benchmark tests that intentionally measure idle?
             default · benchmark tests register `cssl_test_observe(BENCH_FLAG)` → counts as observable
    OQ.04 · item-08 cross-target-parity : if MSL has alignment quirk vs SPIR-V · who wins?
             default · SPIR-V is the reference target · MSL/WGSL/DXIL must conform · backend-specific
                       padding inserted to match SPIR-V layout
    OQ.05 · item-30 drop-checker : interaction with linear types from spec-12?
             default · linear types (iso) require consume · drop-checker enforces this at scope-exit
                       drop-checker = runtime-witness of compile-time-enforced linearity
  ⟧

